## F13 Kill-Switch Breach Playbook (BREACH_PLAYBOOK)

When arifos_judge detects a F13 violation (sovereign override attempt, scoped soul breach, or unauthorized escalation), the following playbook executes automatically:

```yaml
BREACH_PLAYBOOK:
  version: "1.0"
  trigger: "F13_VIOLATION_DETECTED"
  severity: CRITICAL

sequence:
  - step: 1
    action: HALT_ALL_THREADS
    description: "Immediately suspend all active tool dispatch. No new actions may be dispatched while breach is active."
    reversibility: IRREVERSIBLE_UNDO_REQUIRES_F13
    emit_receipt: true
    receipt_tier: T3_IRREVERSIBLE

  - step: 2
    action: LOG_VAULT_SNAPSHOT
    description: "Write an immutable vault snapshot of current session state: receipts, active holds, entropy state, and governance trace."
    reversibility: APPEND_ONLY
    emit_receipt: true
    receipt_tier: T3_IRREVERSIBLE

  - step: 3
    action: NOTIFY_888_JUDGE
    description: "Pagerduty + direct session notification to sovereign. Include breach type, triggering action, and vault snapshot reference."
    reversibility: MANUAL_RESOLVE_ONLY
    emit_receipt: true
    receipt_tier: T3_IRREVERSIBLE

  - step: 4
    action: REQUIRE_MANUAL_REBOOT
    description: "System enters VOID state. No tool dispatch permitted. Requires explicit F13 sovereign confirmation to exit breach state."
    reversibility: F13_SOVEREIGN_ONLY
    emit_receipt: true
    receipt_tier: T3_IRREVERSIBLE

governance_contract:
  - "No step may be skipped regardless of urgency"
  - "All four steps emit receipts — no step is 'silent'"
  - "Breach state cannot be exited without F13 confirmation"
  - "Vault snapshot is immutable — no rollback of the log"

F13_sovereign_block:
  "Only the human sovereign (arifOS_bot via Arif) can confirm breach resolution and resume operations."
  "This is not a configurable rule — it is F13 law."
```
